svg.text:
How draw bissectrix of lines in SVG?
Suppose that line AB is given by equation u1 * x + v1 * y + w1 = 0
Suppose that line CD is given by equation u2 * x + v2 * y + w2 = 0
If a point is on bissectrix, distances to lines are same
Script
// distance to AB is Math.abs( u1 * x + v1 * y + w1) / Math.sqrt ( u1 * u1 + v1 * v1 )
// distance to CD is Math.abs( u2 * x + v2 * y + w2) / Math.sqrt ( u2 * u2 + v2 * v2 )
// With absolute value, we get two equations
// ( u1*x + v1*y + w1) * Math.sqrt ( u2*u2 + v2*v2 ) = ( u2*x + v2*y + w2) * Math.sqrt ( u1*u1 + v1*v1 )
// ( u1*x + v1*y + w1) * Math.sqrt ( u2*u2 + v2*v2 ) =  - ( u2*x + v2*y + w2) * Math.sqrt ( u1*u1 + v1*v1 )
// calcul of equations
u = u1 * Math.sqrt( u2 * u2 + v2 * v2 ) - u2 * Math.sqrt( u1 * u1 + v1 * v1 )
v = v1 * Math.sqrt( u2 * u2 + v2 * v2 ) - v2 * Math.sqrt( u1 * u1 + v1 * v1 )
w = w1 * Math.sqrt( u2 * u2 + v2 * v2 ) - w2 * Math.sqrt( u1 * u1 + v1 * v1 )
// we call function to clip line to viewport
clip_line( u , v , w )
// we get points to draw line in array
MyBiss.setAttributeNS(null,"x1",clip_p[0][0])
MyBiss.setAttributeNS(null,"y1",clip_p[0][1])
MyBiss.setAttributeNS(null,"x2",clip_p[1][0])
MyBiss.setAttributeNS(null,"y2",clip_p[1][1])
// we make same work for second bissectrix
